                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/soci-327" class="program-course-title">
              SOCI 327 Jews in North America (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-35589" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Sociology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Sociology (Arts)              : Understanding of contemporary North American Jewry using findings of sociology and other social sciences. Social, cultural, and political issues of concern to the Jewish community. Specific characteristics of Jewish life in Canada, and Québec in particular, in comparison to the American Jewish experience.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

